Elgeyo Marakwet County Assembly has rejected the Constitution Amendment, 2020 Bill. Seventeen MCAs on Monday voted to reject the Bill, while 15 voted in support of it during a session chaired by speaker Kiplagat Sabulei. The county becomes the third to reject the bill after Baringo and Nandi. Elgeyo Marakwet Governor Alex Tolgos is chairman of the BBI process in Rift Valley and has been lobbying the MCSs to pass the Bill. Uasin Gishu Assembly is also expected to vote on the bill. The region is home to DP William Ruto and most MCAs are allied to him. More follows...